    {
      "id": "1d559c83cab4b0f8f161b833af7f9be478ba1d3e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-03-02 17:08:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI like this change, I think it has improved the code readability. \n\nUnfortunately, a couple of minor issues:\n- why does the updated LIBCFS_DEBUG_MSG_DATA_DECL() macro set msgdata.msg_mask explicitly, unlike all of the other variables being initialized?  It could just use \".msg_mask = mask\" like the others.\n- the CFS_CHECK_STACK() macro should continue to have \"&msgdata\" parameter, and add a \"mask\" parameter, instead of declaring its own msgdata. Otherwise it will double the memory usage by adding an extra msgdata struct for each usage.  It can set msg_mask to D_WARNING if needed and then reset it to the passed \"mask\". Since this happens only rarely it is not a performance issue.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "751afb0c0c858992537a9031ee317502fcf075fe",
      "author": {
