    {
      "id": "97c65900049ef13bd3bb1d82881789e26cd1b2c9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 144,
        "name": "Hongchao Zhang",
        "email": "hongchao@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "Hongchao.zhang"
      },
      "date": "2012-03-03 01:52:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nQ1: why does the updated LIBCFS_DEBUG_MSG_DATA_DECL() macro set msgdata.msg_mask explicitly, unlike all of the other variables being initialized? It could just use \".msg_mask = mask\" like the others.\n\nthere is a compile error for the \"mask\" could be a expression, e.g. \nin function libcfs_socket_connect in libcfs/libcfs/linux/linux-tcpip.c \n\nCDEBUG_LIMIT(*fatal ? D_NETERROR : D_NET,\n               \"Error %d connecting %u.%u.%u.%u/%d -> %u.%u.%u.%u/%d\\n\", rc,\n               HIPQUAD(local_ip), local_port, HIPQUAD(peer_ip), peer_port);\n\nthe mask is \"*fatal ? D_NETERROR : D_NET\", which will cause\n\"error: initializer element is not constant\"\n\n\n Q2: the CFS_CHECK_STACK() macro should continue to have \"&msgdata\" parameter, and add a \"mask\" parameter, instead of declaring its own msgdata. Otherwise it will double the memory usage by adding an extra msgdata struct for each usage. It can set msg_mask to D_WARNING if needed and then reset it to the passed \"mask\". Since this happens only rarely it is not a performance issue.\n\nyes, the independent msgdata is added into CFS_CHECK_STACK \nfor it could change the msg_mask, and CFS_CHECK_STACK is used\nin three places, especially in \"debug_req\" and \"ldlm_lock_debug\"\nit will also affect the other functions, which make the code look not very good",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "5b7a0422e83434ac120e65a7580d7efcc87c1558",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2012-03-03 04:46:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.2/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/24b82cf6-64ea-11e1-ac48-5254004bbbd3).  Ran 13 tests.  No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "20f0d9d62855c34ab4a8c36c5201f0f2a4f47b5c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2012-03-03 06:00:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7: Verified\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.2/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/a9b4513c-64f4-11e1-ac48-5254004bbbd3).  Ran 13 tests.  No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "57c59ce72b898b037e1655ee8544c42a4f18a2b5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-03-04 08:22:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\n> the mask is \"*fatal ? D_NETERROR : D_NET\", which will\n> cause \"error: initializer element is not constant\"\n\nThe number of places that have non-constant masks is very small.  There are 6 callers of CDEBUG_LIMIT, and any callsites that use CDEBUG(mask, ...) that may print to the console (mask = D_ERROR, D_WARNING, D_CONSOLE) should be considered an error because they are not rate-limited, so I'm happy if this turns into a compile-time error.  This will also reduce (but not totally eliminate) the cases where there is a race between one error mask and another.\n\nFor those few sites that do this, they should just be split into two separate calls - one using CERROR() and one using CDEBUG() (or appropriate, as needed).\n\n> the independent msgdata is added into CFS_CHECK_STACK \n> for it could change the msg_mask, and CFS_CHECK_STACK\n> is used in three places, especially in \"debug_req\" and\n> \"ldlm_lock_debug\" it will also affect the other functions,\n> which make the code look not very good\n\nBut the cost of double msgdata structs for every callsite of CDEBUG(), LDLM_DEBUG(), DEBUG_REQ() will be very high.  Passing the mask to CFS_CHECK_STACK() avoids this problem without increasing the stack usage, and the number of times that the stack usage is growing will be very small, and definitely not worth the extra memory usage.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
